{"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.ClassNumber.Finite","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.Pow.Real","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.FreeModule.PID","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Matrix.AbsoluteValue","Mathlib.NumberTheory.ClassNumber.AdmissibleAbsoluteValue","Mathlib.RingTheory.ClassGroup","Mathlib.RingTheory.DedekindDomain.IntegralClosure","Mathlib.RingTheory.Norm"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L397-L416","name":"ClassGroup.fintypeOfAdmissibleOfFinite","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.fintypeOfAdmissibleOfFinite","doc":"The main theorem: the class group of an integral closure `S` of `R` in a\nfinite extension `L` of `K = Frac(R)` is finite if there is an admissible\nabsolute value.\n\nSee also `ClassGroup.fintypeOfAdmissibleOfAlgebraic` where `L` is an\nalgebraic extension of `R`, that includes some extra assumptions.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L375-L387","name":"ClassGroup.fintypeOfAdmissibleOfAlgebraic","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.fintypeOfAdmissibleOfAlgebraic","doc":"The main theorem: the class group of an integral closure `S` of `R` in an\nalgebraic extension `L` is finite if there is an admissible absolute value.\n\nSee also `ClassGroup.fintypeOfAdmissibleOfFinite` where `L` is a finite\nextension of `K = Frac(R)`, supplying most of the required assumptions automatically.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L358-L363","name":"ClassGroup.mkMMem_surjective","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.mkMMem_surjective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L351-L354","name":"ClassGroup.mkMMem","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.mkMMem","doc":"`ClassGroup.mkMMem` is a specialization of `ClassGroup.mk0` to (the finite set of)\nideals that contain `M := ∏ m in finsetApprox L f abs, m`.\nBy showing this function is surjective, we prove that the class group is finite. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L313-L345","name":"ClassGroup.exists_mk0_eq_mk0","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.exists_mk0_eq_mk0","doc":"Each class in the class group contains an ideal `J`\nsuch that `M := Π m ∈ finsetApprox` is in `J`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L306-L308","name":"ClassGroup.ne_bot_of_prod_finsetApprox_mem","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.ne_bot_of_prod_finsetApprox_mem","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L299-L303","name":"ClassGroup.prod_finsetApprox_ne_zero","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.prod_finsetApprox_ne_zero","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L277-L294","name":"ClassGroup.exists_mem_finset_approx'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.exists_mem_finset_approx'","doc":"We can approximate `a / b : L` with `q / r`, where `r` has finitely many options for `L`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L223-L273","name":"ClassGroup.exists_mem_finsetApprox","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.exists_mem_finsetApprox","doc":"We can approximate `a / b : L` with `q / r`, where `r` has finitely many options for `L`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L200-L212","name":"ClassGroup.mem_finsetApprox","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.mem_finsetApprox","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L195-L196","name":"ClassGroup.finsetApprox.zero_not_mem","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.finsetApprox.zero_not_mem","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L190-L192","name":"ClassGroup.finsetApprox","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.finsetApprox","doc":"`finsetApprox` is a finite set such that each fractional ideal in the integral closure\ncontains an element close to `finsetApprox`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L182-L183","name":"ClassGroup.distinctElems","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.distinctElems","doc":"In the following results, we need a large set of distinct elements of `R`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L174-L175","name":"ClassGroup.cardM","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.cardM","doc":"If we have a large enough set of elements in `R^ι`, then there will be a pair\nwhose remainders are close together. We'll show that all sets of cardinality\nat least `cardM bS adm` elements satisfy this condition.\n\nThe value of `cardM` is not at all optimal: for specific choices of `R`,\nthe minimum cardinality can be exponentially smaller.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L143-L160","name":"ClassGroup.exists_min","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.exists_min","doc":"A nonzero ideal has an element of minimal norm. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L114-L137","name":"ClassGroup.norm_lt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.norm_lt","doc":"If the `R`-integral element `a : S` has coordinates `< y` with respect to some basis `b`,\nits norm is strictly less than `normBound abv b * y ^ dim S`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L91-L109","name":"ClassGroup.norm_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.norm_le","doc":"If the `R`-integral element `a : S` has coordinates `≤ y` with respect to some basis `b`,\nits norm is less than `normBound abv b * y ^ dim S`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L73-L86","name":"ClassGroup.normBound_pos","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.normBound_pos","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.lean#L62-L70","name":"ClassGroup.normBound","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/ClassNumber/Finite.html#ClassGroup.normBound","doc":"If `b` is an `R`-basis of `S` of cardinality `n`, then `normBound abv b` is an integer\nsuch that for every `R`-integral element `a : S` with coordinates `≤ y`,\nwe have algebra.norm a ≤ norm_bound abv b * y ^ n`. (See also `norm_le` and `norm_lt`). "}]}